{"lemma":"صُورَةٌ","slug":"صُورَةٌ","root":"ص.#.ر","root_slug":"ص-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صُورَة","root":"صور","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25179"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"form, shape, figure"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"image, picture, photograph"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"copy"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"appearance"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"attribute","tags":["attributive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"manner"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"character"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"face"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an inclination or desire","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an itching on the head","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alternative form of صَوْر (ṣawr, “small palm-trees”)","tags":["alt-of","alternative","obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"While it would be possible to comprehend it from يَصُورُ (yaṣūru, “to make bent towards a shape”), in the same fashion as سُنّة (sunna, “image, figure, form, external appearance”) is from سَنَّ (sanna, “to mold; to establish”), this would require it to be already Central Semitic in view of Hebrew צוּרָה (ṣūrā́, “form, shape”) and Aramaic צוּרְתָא / ܨܘܪܬܐ (ṣūrtā), and the likelihoods are good that we have a borrowing – in Arabic via the latter – from Akkadian 𒄑𒄯 (iṣurtu, “drawing, plan”)."},"ipa":["/sˤuː.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25179","headword_ar":"صُورَةٌ","root":"Swr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Form, fashion, figure, shape,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"semblance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akolN","text_ar":"شَكْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mivaAlN","text_ar":"مِثَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"external state"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; (IAth;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that whereby a thing is sensibly distinguished by men in general, and even by many other animate beings, from other things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Swrp","text_ar":"صورة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man, and of a horse, and of an ass. (B.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An effigy; an image,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a statue; a picture; anything that is formed, fashioned, figured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shaped, after the likeness of any of God's creatures, animate"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inanimate:"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is said that the maker of an effigy, or image, will be punished on the day of resurrection, and will be commanded to put life into it; and that the angels will not enter a house in which is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Swrp","text_ar":"صورة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSaAwiyru","text_ar":"تَصَاوِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  [Hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mental image;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a resemblance, of any object, formed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conceived, by the mind; an idea:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a meaning of frequent occurrence in philosophical works &c.] ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Species;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawoEN","text_ar":"نَوْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b5-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"essence"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that by being which a thing is what it is;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aggregate of properties"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"qualities, whereby a thing is what it is;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaqiyqapN","text_ar":"حَقِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAth:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"specific character;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that whereby a thing is mentally distinguished by particular persons, not by the vulgar, from other things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Swrp","text_ar":"صورة"},{"kind":"text","text":"by which a man is specially distinguished, consisting in reason and thought and other distinctive attributes: (B:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a quality, an attribute, a property;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a description,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aggregate of the qualities"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attributes"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"properties,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state, condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SifapN","text_ar":"صِفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAth, Msb, K:) as when you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suwrapu AlA^amori ka*aA","text_ar":"صُورَةُ الاَمْرِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The quality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the thing is of such a kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (IAth, Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suwrapu AlmasoA^alapi","text_ar":"صُورَةُ المَسْاَلَةِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA","text_ar":"كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The description, statement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"form, of the question is of such a kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) and so in the saying of the Prophet,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ataAniY All~ayolapa rab~iY fiY","text_ar":"اَتَانِى اللَّيْلَةَ رَبِّى فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHosani SuwrapK","text_ar":"اَحْسَنِ صُورَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My Lord came to me to-night in a most goodly state"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Swrp","text_ar":"صورة"},{"kind":"text","text":"may here refer to the Prophet, and may mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"external state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner of being,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth.) ―         -b6-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an action. (IAth.) ―         -b7-  The pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuwarN","text_ar":"صُوَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiwarN","text_ar":"صِوَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuwrN","text_ar":"صُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, K;) the second of which is rare, and by some disallowed. (MF.) ―         -b8-  The saying of the Prophet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqa A@ll~`hu A=dama EalaY Suwratihi","text_ar":"خَلَقَ ا@للّٰهُ ا=دَمَ عَلَى صُورَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may mean that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God created Adam in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Swrp","text_ar":"صورة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"form"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, God,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"originated and ordained;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Swrp","text_ar":"صورة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, Adam. (M.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuwrapN","text_ar":"صُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in a trad. cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHar~amN","text_ar":"مُحَرَّمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; in which it is said that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Swrp","text_ar":"صورة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pronounced sacred, i. e. that it is not to be slapped: and in another, in which it is said that the Prophet disliked marking the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Swrp","text_ar":"صورة"},{"kind":"text","text":"with a hot iron. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","IAth","B","Msb","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}